        <link:link rdf:resource="#item_5806"/>
        <dc:subject>
           <z:AutomaticTag><rdf:value>/unread</rdf:value></z:AutomaticTag>
        </dc:subject>
        <dc:title>Virtual stereo vision-based localization and 3D mesh mapping for dual UAV systems</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>Simultaneous Localization and Mapping (SLAM) has been extensively applied to solve the problem of robot localization and mapping without absolute position measure ments. Visual sensors are widely used in odometry techniques due to their low cost and richer information content. How ever,when robots operate far from the scene (e.g., high-altitude UAVs), visual-inertial odometry (VIO) positioning accuracy de grades significantly. This compromises the balance between au tonomous precision and rapid scene understanding. To address this issue, we propose a collaborative dual-UAV localization and real-time scene reconstruction framework for high-altitude op erations.By utilizing inter-UAV visual overlap observations and wireless ranging constraints, we propose a collaborative decen tralized trajectory localization and global map point consistency optimization scheme. Our solution achieves high-altitude precise positioning and maintains dual-UAV observation consistency, enabling real-time construction of large-scale navigable maps. Evaluation results in photorealistic simulated environments demonstrate the superior accuracy of our approach in high altitude localization and scene reconstruction.</dcterms:abstract>
        <dc:date>2025-12-3</dc:date>
